SANParks recently announced the following investment opportunities for public-private partnerships: Opportunity for a private party to operate the Skukuza Safari Lodge and the Nombolo Mdhluli Conference Centre in the Kruger National Park through a management agreement for a period of 10 years. Bid submission date: August 19, 2022, at 11:00. Tender documentation will be available from the SANParks website, under the ”Tenders” section: https://www.sanparks.org/groups/tenders/. Enquiries: Jeanette Greyvensteyn, project officer, jeanette.greyvensteyn@sanparks.org. Opportunity for a private party to operate a spa facility in the Golden Gate Highlands National Park for a period of 10 years. Enquiries: Banele Malie, project officer, banele.malie@sanparks.org. Opportunity for a private party to operate a kiosk and curio shop at the Dinosaur Interpretation Centre in the Golden Gate Highlands National Park for a period of eight years. Enquiries: Banele Malie, project officer, banele.malie@sanparks.org. Opportunity for a private party to operate the Cape Point’s tourism facilities, including a restaurant, three retail shops and funicular offerings within the southern section of Table Mountain National Park for a period of 40 years. Enquiries: Wendy Davids, project officer, wendy.davids@sanparks.org. Opportunity for a private party to operate a restaurant and retail facility in the Augrabies Falls National Park. Enquiries: James Daniels, project officer, james.daniels@sanparks.org. Opportunity for a private party to operate a spa facility in the northern Kruger National Park. Enquiries: James Daniels, project officer, james.daniels@sanparks.org. Bids are to be submitted to the SANParks head office, 643 Leyds Street, Muckleneuk, Pretoria. No late bids will be accepted.